HEADWORD: Atmometer
<hw>At*mom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ smoke,
vapor + <ets>-meter</ets>: cf. F. <ets>atmom⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>.]</ety>
<def>An instrument for measuring the rate of evaporation from a moist
surface; an evaporometer.</def> <rj><au>Huxley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

